	(text "- Pins PN[0..12] are used for NOR flash interfacing via XSPI interface\n- CSI and USB buses are in the Analog_Unit sheet.\n- FMC pins will NOT be put on headers. They are internal only, and\n   are used to connect the 128Mb IS42 SDRAM\n- Some UART headers (1, 2, 3) are 'USART' and can operate synchronously.\n   However, some USART clock pins have been used up, so consult CubeMX\n   first.\n- DP and DM pins (also CC pins) for the USB interface are in the\n   Analog schematic.\n- 2k Ohm resistors have been used to pullup I2C pins, layout deems that\n   any 1206 size resistor should work. Same for oscillator caps.\n- HDP pins (Hardware Debug) will be connected to upward facing headers,\n   NOT connected to the main board. So even though the connectors will\n   will be in the connectors sheet, they are not designed to connect\n   to the main board.\n- CSI connector will also be on the top of the PCB alone. Not going\n   to main board.\n- All non-power pins can be configured as GPIO's, but only timer pins\n   can operate as analog input/output pins, generating PWM."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 208.534 24.384 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 0.1588)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "47fffd96-a760-4bca-85c1-d85982e6152c")
	)
